After calculating the BA for the complete data set, which is not on a uniform grid, the BA is interpolated to a uniform grid for qualitative and quantitative interpretation (Fig. 2). There are many options for the interpolation, as noted in Enriquez et al. (1983), but we chose to use the method of minimum curvature which is a standard choice in the literature (Mickus et al. 1991). Further, unless specifically noted, for the data processing of the gravimetric data we use the Geosoft Oasis Montaj® software package, where we indicate in each case the equations used and point to the relevant references, noting that a good overview is in Blakely (1995). Finally, for obtaining the BA we assume a background density of 2500 kg/cm3\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
