The regional anomaly map shows a regular decrease in the gravitational field from North to South (Fig. 3A). This gravity gradient presents a slope of about of 1 mGal/km. The residual anomaly map (Fig. 3B) enhances the local anomalies shown on the Bouguer anomaly map, the tendency is mainly a series of high anomalies surrounded in the East (Guelma) and West (Hammam Debagh) alternating with low anomalies. The values of the gravity field range between -19.206\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
